\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. T. balcanicus} Velen.,{\i  Abh. Böhm. Ges. Wiss.} ser. 7, {\b 1}({\b 8}): 28 (1886). Biennial with a usually simple rootstock. Stems 15-60 cm, usually branched, glabrous or sparsely floccose. Leaves narrowly linear, widened at base. Peduncles not inflated; involucral bracts 4-5, about as long as ligules. Ligules purplish-violet. Achenes c. 2 cm, squamose-muricate; beak about as long as body, distinctly clavate. Pappus about as long as achene. 2n = 12.{\i  Rocky places. • N. & C. parts of Balkan peninsula; S.W. Romania.} Al Bu Gr Ju Rm Tu.
